Term	                                      Description
Smart Queue Management System	              A digital system used to manage and monitor customer queues in bank branches
Bank Customer                       	      A person visiting the bank to avail services
Token	                                      A virtual queue number assigned to a customer
Queue                                     	A waiting line of customers for bank services
Teller	                                    Bank staff responsible for serving customers
Admin	                                      Bank manager or authorized staff who manages the system
Service Counter	                            A designated desk where bank services are provided
Queue Status	                              Current position and progress of the queue
Notification	                              Alert sent to a customer when their turn approaches
Dashboard                                 	Admin interface used to monitor queue performance
SRS	                                        Software Requirements Specification document
UI (User Interface)	                        The visual interface through which users interact with the system
Authentication	                            Process of verifying user identity before system access
Report	                                    Summary of queue statistics such as customers served and waiting time
